= lesson 12: requests

In Toki Pona, a sentence with #strong[ůĪ§ß li] is a statement of fact. But
sometimes instead of making statements of fact, we want to make requests.
Requests are how we tell other people what we want to happen. In a request,
instead of #strong[ůĪ§ß li], we use #strong[ůĪ•Ą o]:

#list((
  word("ůĪ•Ą", "o", "starts a request, command, instruction, wish"),
  sentence("ůĪ§éůĪ§ßůĪ•†ůĪ§ČůĪ•Ď", "ilo li sitelen e pipi.", "The phone is showing a bug."),
  sentence("ůĪ§éůĪ•ĄůĪ•†ůĪ§ČůĪ•ī", "ilo o sitelen e waso!", "Oh phone, please show a bird!"),
))

